OpenMC Surrogate Prediction Data & XML Configurations

This repository contains the data files used for surrogate model predictions alongside their corresponding OpenMC XML configuration files. 


The data in this repository was generated using specific OpenMC transport simulation parameters. To ensure accurate surrogate predictions and compatibility, the following configuration was used:

OpenMC Version: 0.14.0
Batches: 120
Particles per Batch: 50,000

Important Usage Instructions

To successfully use these files and replicate or build upon these results, you must use the exact same setup. Running the XML files or processing the surrogate data with a different version of OpenMC or different history parameters (batches/particles) may lead to prediction errors. 

Please ensure your local environment is running OpenMC v0.14.0 and that your run settings strictly maintain 120 batches and 50,000 particles.
